<h2>Latest News</h2>

<h3><a href="http://www.gnome.org/projects/outreach/a11y/">GNOME Outreach Program: Accessibility</a></h3>
<p>The GNOME Foundation is running an <a href="http://www.gnome.org/projects/outreach/a11y/">accessibility outreach program</a>, offering USD$50,000 to be split among individuals. This program will promote software accessibility awareness among the GNOME community as well as harden and improve the overall quality of the GNOME accessibility offering. Read the full <a href="http://www.gnome.org/press/releases/gop-a11y.html">announcement</a>, the <a href="http://www.gnome.org/projects/outreach/a11y/rules/">contest rules</a> and apply for some of the <a href="http://www.gnome.org/projects/outreach/a11y/tasks/">tasks</a>!.</p>

<h3><a href="http://www.gnome.org/projects/ghop/">Google Highly Open Participation Contest</a></h3>
<p>GNOME is participating to the <a href="http://code.google.com/opensource/ghop/2007-8">Google Highly Open Participation</a> Contest. If you are a pre-university student and you want to lean more, you can read the <a href="http://code.google.com/opensource/ghop/2007-8/rules.html">contest rules</a> and the <a href="http://code.google.com/opensource/ghop/2007-8/faqs.html">frequently asked questions</a>. And then, <a href="http://www.gnome.org/projects/ghop/">get started!</a></p>

<h3><a href="http://www.gnome.org/start/2.20/notes/en">GNOME 2.20 Released!</a></h3>
<p>The GNOME desktop and platform received many improvements and new
features. Learn more about this release through the detailed 
<a href="http://www.gnome.org/start/2.20/notes/en/">release notes</a>.</p>

</div>

<div id="bottomLeftRight">

<h2>Upcoming Events</h2>

<h3><a href="http://www.guadec.org/">GUADEC 2008</a></h3>
<i>July 7-12, 2008; Istanbul, Turkey</i>
<p>At the annual European GNOME Conference, GNOME hackers from all across the
globe will gather and show off new cool technologies, party and discuss the
future direction of the project.
<p>Keynote speakers include Leisa Reichelt and Matt Webb, who are both heavily
involved in user experience, and Eric Sink, founder of AbiSource and software
development business entrepreneur!</p>
<p>Do you have anything interesting to show the rest of the GNOME Community?
<a href="http://guadec.org/guadec08/public/cfp/1">Send in your talk proposal</a>
before Sunday 30th March.</p>

